    "created_at": "2018-03-21T02:56:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-03-21T02:56:55Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@jiangtaoli2016 Hi, can you check if this api proposal does make sense, please? It's heavy influenced by existing server-side golang session ticket API.\r\n\r\n1. Add one more private field to `grpc_ssl_server_certificate_config` structure: list of session ticket encryption keys (STEKs).\r\n2. First key in the list is used to encrypt new tickets\r\n3. All keys are used for decrypting old tickets (to support graceful ticket rotation)\r\n4. Add function to set STEKs to config after its construction but before giving it to the server.\r\n5. Perform `sha512` on every key, use first 16 bytes as \"name\", next 16 bytes as \"aes key\" for encryption, next 16 bytes as \"hmac key\" for signing.\r\n\r\n```\r\ntypedef struct {\r\n    uint8_t key[32];\r\n} grpc_ssl_session_ticket_key;\r\ngrpc_ssl_server_certificate_config_set_session_ticket_keys(\r\n    grpc_ssl_server_certificate_config* config,\r\n    grpc_ssl_session_ticket_key session_ticket_keys,\r\n    size_t num_session_ticket_keys);\r\n...\r\nauto config = grpc_ssl_server_certificate_config_create(...);\r\ngrpc_ssl_server_certificate_config_set_session_ticket_keys(config, keys.data(), keys.size());\r\nauto credentials = grpc_ssl_server_credentials_create_options_using_config(..., config);\r\n```"
